10:39.848 --> 10:41.099
They're rerunning the concerto.

10:41.183 --> 10:42.726
In memory of Mad Moira.

10:42.809 --> 10:45.020
Oh, my God, will you stop
calling her that?

10:45.103 --> 10:46.688
She carved symbols all over
the wall and threw herself

10:46.772 --> 10:48.315
out a third-floor window.
Plus, she talked to what,

10:48.398 --> 10:50.150
like, no one
the entire time she was here?

10:50.233 --> 10:51.193
And she was ambidextrous.

10:51.276 --> 10:52.903
And that's relevant because...?

10:52.986 --> 10:54.279
She wrote with both hands.

10:54.363 --> 10:56.365
Inside out,
like Leonardo da Vinci.

10:56.448 --> 10:58.075
The chick was just
new levels of freaky.

10:58.158 --> 10:59.201
She was brilliant.

11:00.452 --> 11:02.996
It's just weird,
the competition.

11:03.080 --> 11:04.915
I mean, she died six weeks ago.

11:04.998 --> 11:06.708
Yeah, it's kind of soon,

11:06.792 --> 11:08.335
but the showcase is
a big opportunity.

11:08.418 --> 11:10.712
I mean, someone else
should get a chance.

11:10.796 --> 11:12.047
Yeah, I heard Juilliard's
sending scouts this year.

11:12.130 --> 11:13.757
- Really?
- And my golden gal

11:13.840 --> 11:16.218
is gonna wow them all again
when she plays her concerto.

11:16.301 --> 11:18.095
