19:14.028 --> 19:15.697
Break a leg.

20:03.578 --> 20:05.288
Jules, open the fucking door!

20:05.371 --> 20:06.915
Jules, come on!

20:06.998 --> 20:09.000
We're gonna be late! Jules!

20:10.543 --> 20:11.836
Wombie, you owe...

20:11.920 --> 20:13.880
Whoa.

20:16.174 --> 20:17.800
-Fuck.
-Oh, this is hilarious.

20:17.884 --> 20:20.345
Don't you keep, like,
a calendar or something?

20:20.428 --> 20:22.305
No, it wasn't supposed to...

20:22.388 --> 20:23.723
Fuck!

20:24.807 --> 20:26.059
Hey, hey.

20:26.142 --> 20:27.310
Come here. Look at me.

20:27.393 --> 20:28.436
Hey.

20:28.519 --> 20:30.313
Head in the game.

20:30.396 --> 20:32.065
Okay?

20:33.316 --> 20:34.984
Okay.

20:35.068 --> 20:37.570
You're fine. Come on.
Let's tampon and go.

21:04.430 --> 21:06.099
Vi.

21:08.851 --> 21:10.812
-Vi.
-Jules, not now.

22:34.562 --> 22:36.272
Well read, Andy.

22:36.355 --> 22:37.732
Anyone left?

22:37.815 --> 22:39.734
I haven't played.

22:39.817 --> 22:40.818
Juliet.

22:40.902 --> 22:42.361
Come on down.

22:45.198 --> 22:46.282
Come here.

22:46.365 --> 22:47.617
So...

22:47.700 --> 22:50.745
it says here
you're also treating us

22:50.828 --> 22:52.622
to Saint-Saëns.

22:53.706 --> 22:55.500
Is that right?

23:01.422 --> 23:03.299
When you're ready.

26:44.770 --> 26:47.523
Juliet.

26:47.606 --> 26:49.150
Can you hear me?

26:56.157 --> 26:57.616
There she is.

26:59.452 --> 27:00.828
We're waiting on the nurse.

27:00.911 --> 27:01.912
What happened?

27:01.996 --> 27:03.622
You passed out.

27:05.207 --> 27:07.084
How'd I play? Was I good?

27:07.168 --> 27:08.627
You did great.

27:08.711 --> 27:11.255
Roger says you've been taking
propranolol.

27:11.339 --> 27:13.674
-Is that for anxiety?
-Yeah.

27:13.758 --> 27:15.343
You know, with recent events,

27:15.426 --> 27:18.429
you may be feeling
a little destabilized.

27:18.512 --> 27:20.389
Is there anything on your mind?

27:20.473 --> 27:22.600
Odd thoughts?
Troubling thoughts?

27:22.683 --> 27:24.685
No.

27:24.769 --> 27:26.854
Nothing.

27:29.523 --> 27:32.318
So, remember, E-flat major.

27:39.367 --> 27:41.118
An accidental there.

27:42.787 --> 27:45.498
Find where it is.

27:48.584 --> 27:51.545
Same thing again.

27:51.629 --> 27:55.257
And for the finish, do not
forget to name the cadence.

28:01.806 --> 28:03.891
Turn in
your transcriptions to me

28:03.974 --> 28:06.394
by the end of the day,
ladies and gentlemen.

28:09.271 --> 28:10.648
Juliet, you good?

28:10.731 --> 28:12.775
-You saw the nurse?
-Yeah. It was just nerves.

28:12.858 --> 28:14.151
You know, you played well.

28:14.235 --> 28:15.611
Has Roger got you doing
something different?

28:17.988 --> 28:20.783
No, I, uh, guess
I just felt inspired.

28:20.866 --> 28:22.326
Well, whatever it is,
it's working.

28:22.410 --> 28:24.495
Keep up the momentum, okay?

28:24.578 --> 28:26.247
Okay.

28:29.291 --> 28:30.751
Vi.

28:31.877 --> 28:33.838
Vi, come on.

28:39.343 --> 28:41.178
Vi, stop.

28:41.262 --> 28:42.847
I'm sorry. I fucked up.

28:42.930 --> 28:44.473
I should've told you
I changed my entry.

28:44.557 --> 28:46.058
Changed your entry?
You stole my piece.

28:46.142 --> 28:47.685
What, is something funny?

28:47.768 --> 28:49.311
No, just...

28:49.395 --> 28:52.022
you're the one
who told me to switch.

28:52.106 --> 28:53.899
To Beethoven or Grieg
or freaking Rachmaninoff.

28:53.983 --> 28:55.568
I mean, you literally had
hundreds of options.

28:55.651 --> 28:57.862
-I know. I just, I didn't think.
-No, you didn't.

28:57.945 --> 28:59.613
Because if you had, you'd have
realized the only person

28:59.697 --> 29:01.866
you were embarrassing out there
was yourself.

29:01.949 --> 29:03.659
I already knew you were jealous.

29:03.742 --> 29:06.745
Now, thanks to your little
stunt, everybody else does, too.

30:47.346 --> 30:48.806
That's a really good point.

30:48.889 --> 30:51.350
-Yeah, but they're both
in E major. -Right.

30:52.726 --> 30:54.520
How are you feeling?

30:54.603 --> 30:56.146
Good.

31:03.487 --> 31:06.240
So, you went for
the Saint-Saëns.

31:07.950 --> 31:09.952
You know,

31:10.035 --> 31:14.164
when I suggested that
you stick with the Mozart,

31:14.248 --> 31:16.917
I had your best interests
at heart.

31:18.168 --> 31:20.754
Still, I suppose it's behind us.

31:27.761 --> 31:30.139
-Are you proud of me?
-Proud?

31:30.222 --> 31:32.766
Of course I'm... proud of you.

31:34.101 --> 31:35.603
Four years
we've studied together.

31:35.686 --> 31:37.187
You're a fine player.

31:37.271 --> 31:38.939
Right.

31:40.774 --> 31:42.651
What if I could be more?

31:42.735 --> 31:44.903
I don't follow.

31:44.987 --> 31:46.905
What if I could be
more than fine?

31:46.989 --> 31:48.365
What if I could be great?

31:48.449 --> 31:50.492
What if all I needed
was a chance to compete,

31:50.576 --> 31:51.952
to prove myself?

31:52.036 --> 31:54.079
Julie.

31:54.163 --> 31:56.332
I salute your ambition.

31:56.415 --> 31:58.709
But if we all played
concertmaster,

31:58.792 --> 32:00.502
we'd never have an orchestra.

32:00.586 --> 32:02.796
Now, you're a good player.

32:02.880 --> 32:04.548
I believe in you.

32:04.632 --> 32:07.384
But you have to manage
your expectations.

32:07.468 --> 32:11.180
We can't all be off
chasing concerti.

32:11.263 --> 32:12.931
So, what should I be chasing?

32:13.015 --> 32:14.475
Teaching posts.

32:14.558 --> 32:16.060
Chamber work.

32:16.143 --> 32:18.437
You are a sensitive accompanist.

32:18.520 --> 32:20.564
Schools are always looking.

32:20.648 --> 32:23.442
"A sensitive accompanist"?

32:27.821 --> 32:32.660
I was practicing three hours
a day when I was nine.

32:32.743 --> 32:34.912
I've never owned a PlayStation.

32:34.995 --> 32:36.914
Never smoked a cigarette.

32:36.997 --> 32:39.041
Do you know the average age

32:39.124 --> 32:41.627
people lose their virginity
in this country?

32:42.961 --> 32:44.922
It's 17.

32:45.005 --> 32:49.301
Next month, I will be
a statistical fucking anomaly.

32:49.385 --> 32:51.845
I have given my entire life
to music,

32:51.929 --> 32:54.098
and you think I did it
so I could sit

32:54.181 --> 32:55.683
at some school hall keyboard

32:55.766 --> 32:57.768
eating some seventh-grade
part-timer's shit?

33:03.065 --> 33:04.525
Did you vote for her?

33:05.693 --> 33:07.069
What?

33:07.152 --> 33:09.405
The competition.

33:09.488 --> 33:11.615
Did you vote for Vi?

33:13.117 --> 33:15.077
Vivian...

33:15.160 --> 33:17.329
was the more accomplished
musician.

33:19.415 --> 33:22.167
Now, let's put this behind us.

33:23.252 --> 33:25.212
No.

33:25.295 --> 33:27.256
I've outgrown you, Roger.

33:27.339 --> 33:28.465
Outgrown me?

33:28.549 --> 33:30.467
Don't act dumb.

33:30.551 --> 33:31.969
I know it. You know it.

33:32.052 --> 33:33.762
If you were
a half-decent teacher,

33:33.846 --> 33:36.223
you would've passed me on
a long time ago.

33:36.306 --> 33:37.558
And Juilliard?

33:37.641 --> 33:39.351
My fault, too, is it?

33:39.435 --> 33:41.270
I told you, widen the net.

33:41.353 --> 33:44.189
